2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper introduces a caching efficiency metric and analyzes the impact of caching on network cost and spectral efficiency, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses caching of content, which is related to multimedia. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the impact of caching on user-perceived QoS, which is related to social and information networks. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the discussion of interference and signal reception may have some relevance to cryptography and security in wireless networks.
